comment.author: 21624712@N07
comment._content: This is the Druitt Street side of Sydney Town Hall where the major parties have their volunteers handling enquiries for absentee voting. I remember working in this location in the late sixties and I imagine they still have a similar set up. Every vote counts.

comment.author: 52555726@N08
comment._content: When I worked for the Sydney City Council from the 70s to the 90s, I remember booths being set up on the other side. Between the Townhall and St.Andrews Cathedral, at voting time for the different parties.
